dict.string: Paste email address into front most app

on run argv set targetMessage to item 1 of argv set targetBuddyPhone to (system attribute "number") tell application "System Events" tell application "Messages" to activate tell process "Messages" click menu item "New Message" of menu "file" of menu bar 1 set input to targetMessage as text delay 1 keystroke targetBuddyPhone keystroke return end tell end tell
tell application "System Events" to click text area 1 of scroll area 4 of splitter group 1 of window "Messages" of application process "Messages" set the clipboard to targetMessage tell application "System Events" to keystroke "v" using command down try tell application "System Events" to keystroke return on error errMsg return "Error: Make sure that you have paired iPhone and Mac and enabled 'Send as SMS' in Messages preferences on your iPhone" end try end run
Type the message that you wish to send to {var:number}

on alfred_script(q) set tout to 5 set t to 0 repeat while t < tout tell application "System Events" set facetime_running to count (every process whose name is "FaceTime") end tell if facetime_running is 1 then try tell application "System Events" set frontWindow to front window of application process "FaceTime" delay .6 # needed to avoid weird flickering stuff. Try increasing if you still see it on your system click button "Call" of frontWindow exit repeat end tell end try else delay 0.1 end if set t to t + 0.1 end repeat end alfred_script

#!/usr/bin/python # encoding: utf-8
import sys import os from workflow import Workflow3
wf = Workflow3() log = wf.logger
query = os.environ['action'] log.debug(query)
order = wf.stored_data('bp-order')
# Get positions and data of item before nindex, pindex = order.index(query), order.index(query)-1 pdata = order[order.index(query)-1]
# Update the list order[pindex] = query order[nindex] = pdata
wf.store_data('bp-order', order)
sys.stdout.write("")

Search Bluepages using "bp" as keyword. Use cmd/alt/ctrl to get alternative options on the first response. - cmd = Directly open the Bluepages profile in a browser - alt = Send an email to the selected profile using IBM Verse - ctrl = Paste email address of the profile into front most app and copy email to clipboard - shift = Copy email address to clipboard
If you have the Sametime client installed you will be presented with additional options after selecting a profile. - Open chat if online - Call office or mobile using Sametime Unified Telephony (w3 help http://ibm.biz/sutinfo )
You can also update the workflow with an Hotkey to search Bluepages on any selected text.
Use with your Pushbullet API https://www.pushbullet.com/#settings/account to send text messages via your Pushbullet phone app
